HEADWORD: Animalism
<hw>An"i*mal*ism</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>animalisme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The state, activity, or enjoyment of
animals; mere animal life without intellectual or moral qualities or
objectives; preoccupation with sensual, physical, or carnal
pleasures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>animalistic</ent>⟦br⟧
